This paper deals with the problem of efficiently computing the results of information extraction from an input document, which is a common problem in natural language processing and database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses enumeration algorithms and complexity bounds, which are typical topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm that uses automata, which is a common technique in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
